model_explanation: S1 says that Sue is the only person who received apples from Sam, but S2 contradicts that by stating that Rob also received apples, so the two statements conflict.
if Sam only gave apples to Bill, that means Mary didn’t get apples. So S2 is entailed by S1.
S1 says that Mary is the only person who received oranges, while S2 contradicts this by saying Ellen also received oranges.
if Ellen is the only one who got apples, then Tom did not get apples, which makes S2 entailed by S1.
S1 limits Sam’s giving of bananas to only Rob, but says nothing about oranges, so whether Sam gave oranges to Rob or not is independent of S1. Therefore, S2 is independent of S1.
if Bill only got bananas, he didn’t get grapes. So S2 is entailed by S1.
if Ellen only got oranges, she didn’t get grapes. So S2 is entailed by S1.
S1 specifies only Mary got bananas, but says nothing about Ellen and bananas, so S2 is independent of S1.
if only Bill got bananas, then Tom couldn’t have gotten any. So S2 is entailed by S1.
if Sue only got oranges, she didn’t get grapes. So S2 is entailed by S1.
